## Getting Started

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm run build
```

This compiles the TypeScript sources into the `dist/` directory.

## Loading in Chrome / Edge

1. Run `pnpm run build`.
2. Open `chrome://extensions` (or `edge://extensions`).
3. Enable **Developer mode**.
4. Click **Load unpacked** and select the project folder.

## Loading in Firefox (temporary)

1. Run `pnpm run build`.
2. Open `about:debugging#/runtime/this-firefox`.
3. Click **Load Temporary Add-on...**.
4. Select `manifest.json` in the project root.

For publishing to AMO or the Chrome Web Store, you will typically package the `manifest.json`, `dist/`, and any static assets into a zip file and upload it through the vendor portal.

## Project Structure

```text
.
├─ manifest.json        # Browser extension manifest (MV3-oriented)
├─ src/
│  ├─ background.mts    # Background service worker entry
│  ├─ popup/
│  │  ├─ index.html     # Toolbar popup UI
│  │  └─ main.mts       # Popup script
│  └─ options/
│     ├─ index.html     # Configuration UI
│     └─ main.mts       # Options page script
└─ __tests__/
   └─ background.test.mts
```

## Scripts

- `pnpm run build` – Compile TypeScript to `dist/`.
- `pnpm run dev` – Watch-mode TypeScript compilation.
- `pnpm test` – Run unit tests with Vitest.
- `pnpm test:e2e` – Run end-to-end tests with Playwright (requires build).
- `pnpm run dev:chrome` – Launch Chrome with the extension loaded (dev mode).
- `pnpm run dev:firefox` – Launch Firefox with the extension loaded (using `web-ext`).
- `pnpm run lint` – Lint source files.

## Testing

### Unit Tests
Run fast, isolated unit tests with Vitest:
```bash
pnpm test
```

### E2E Tests (Playwright)
Run integration tests in headless browsers:
```bash
pnpm test:e2e
```
This builds the extension and runs Playwright tests defined in `__tests__/e2e`.

### Dockerized Testing (Recommended)
To ensure a clean environment and test against multiple browsers without local setup issues:

```bash
docker-compose up --build
```
This will:
1. Build a fresh Docker container.
2. Install dependencies and build the extension inside the container.
3. Run Playwright tests against Chromium and Firefox.
4. Exit with success/failure code.

### AI-Driven Testing (Stagehand)
This project includes a placeholder for [Stagehand](https://github.com/browserbasehq/stagehand), an AI-powered testing library.
1. Set your `STAGEHAND_API_KEY` in `.env` or environment.
2. Enable the placeholder test in `__tests__/e2e/usecases/stagehand-placeholder.test.mts`.

